# Testing conventions

## Placement

- Unit spec beside implementation: `foo.service.ts` + `foo.service.spec.ts`
- Contract tests: `packages/contracts/src/*.spec.ts`
- API integration: `apps/api/test/**/*.e2e.ts`
- Browser e2e: `apps/admin/e2e/`, `apps/client/e2e/`
- UI RTL: `packages/ui/src/**/*.spec.tsx`

## New feature rule

Do not commit production code without matching tests in the same change:

- API `application/` or `interface/` → module `*.spec.ts` or `apps/api/test/*.e2e.ts`
- `packages/contracts` source → `*.spec.ts`
- `packages/ui` component → sibling `*.spec.tsx`
- Admin/client `features/` → Playwright e2e or unit spec

Pre-commit runs `scripts/check-staged-has-tests.mjs`. Bypass only for emergencies: `SKIP_TEST_CHECK=1`.

## TDD flow

1. QA / agent writes failing tests first (see `docs/agent/AGENTS.md`)
2. Implement until green
3. Prefer behavior assertions over implementation details

## Visual feedback

- `pnpm test:dashboard` — coverage + Playwright HTML hub (like Swagger for tests)
- `pnpm test:ui` — Vitest interactive runner (API)
